  <title>Exercise</title>
  
  <exercise>
    <p>
      The SI unit of energy is <m>J = kg m^{2} s^{-2}</m>; that of speed v is <m>m s^{-1}</m> 
      and of acceleration a is <m>m s^{-2}</m>. Which of the formulae for kinetic energy (K) 
      given below can you rule out on the basis of dimensional arguments (m stands for the
      mass of the body):
      <ol marker ="a.">
        <li>
          <m>K = m^{2}v^{3}</m>
        </li>
        <li><m>K = (1/2)mv^{2}</m></li>
        <li><m>K = ma</m></li>
        <li><m>K = (3/16)mv^{2}t</m></li>
        <li><m>K = (1/2)mv^{2}+ ma</m></li>
      </ol>
      </p>
  </exercise>
 
