<exercise>
  <p>
    Which of the following pair of physical quantities does not have same dimensional formula.
  </p>
<ol marker="a.">
  <li> <p>  Work and Torque, </p> </li>
  <li> <p>Impulse and Linear momentum,</p> </li>
<li><p> Angular momentum and Planck's constant,</p> </li>
<li><p>Tension and Surface tension.</p></li>
</ol>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <p>
      If the equation of state of gas is expressed as 
      <me>
        \left(P+\frac{a}{V^{2}}\right)\left(V-b\right)=RT.
      </me>
     Find the dimensions of a and b. 
    </p>
    <hint>
      <p>
       <m>\frac{a}{V^{2}}</m> has the same dimension as of P, and b has the same dimension as V.
      </p>
    </hint>
  </exercise>

